==English==
===Etymology===
[[sheep]] + [[shag]] - originally military slang. first used in the 1950s

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# {{UK}}, {{slang}} A man who engages in or is said to engage in [[sexual intercourse]] with [[sheep]]; usually used as a slur for a rural person seen as unsophisticated.
#:''She is now back and planning a Victory Parade not to mention her own visit to the newly reconquered territories to receive the homage of the grateful '''sheepshaggers''', all fifty-nine of them.'' -- ''Private Eye'' 2 July 1982, 11/1
#:''Who are you calling a '''sheepshagger'''?'' -- Ian Pattison ''More Rab C. Nesbitt Scripts'' (1992) 62
#:''I used to know a Rockburn once... He was in the '''Sheep Shaggers'''.'' -- Mark Bence-Jones ''Paradise Escaped'' (1958) iv. 73